SIMPLE: quinquagesima
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quinquagesima
<hw>Quin`qua*ges"i*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>quinquagesimus</ets> the fiftieth, akin to <ets>quinquaginta</ets>
fifty, <ets>quinque</ets> five. See <er>Five</er>.]</ety>
<def>Fiftieth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Quinquagesima Sunday</b></col>, <cd>the Sunday which is
the fiftieth day before Easter, both days being included in the
reckoning; -- called also <altname>Shrove
Sunday</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quinquangular</ent>⟦br⟧
